@NODE intro "Introduction"

	Introduction
	------------
	
  WolfHTML is a simple CLI program that generates a 3-D step maze (similar to Dungeon Master,
Alternate Reality series, etc...) from a 2-d map drawn as an ascii .txt file. All the "rooms"
in  the step-maze are .html files (of webpages) making it easy to upload onto your website.
I've checked the maze output with Ibrowse, Aweb, and Voyager, and they all seem to render it
properly. 

  Originally I was inspired to write it to show up my brother, who wrote his maze by hand
(http://www.zenzizenzizenzic.com/). This way I could draw up a far more complex maze than him,
and upload it in a fractino of the time he could redo his.
  
  
  @{"Back" link MAIN}
@ENDNODE

@NODE usage "Command Usage"

	Command Usage
	-------------
  Wolfhmtml is pretty easy to use, even for a CLI program. Here's a list of the options and the 
format. Click on whatever argument you want more info on.

Wolfhtml @{"filename" link filename}, @{"compass" link compass} @{"minimap" link minimap} @{"mapfile" link mapfile} @{"noinfofile" link noinfofile} @{"htm" link htm} @{"norooms" link norooms} @{"maplink" link maplink}

Also, there are several files needed for wolfhtml to work properly. They're all in the sample/ directory, heres a description of them.

sample/
 |
 \+-@{"map.maz" link maze}   = ascii format maze. (.maz extention not important)
  +-@{"102.dor" link door}   = door link file.
  +-left.gif  = .gif image of left arrow
  +-right.gif = .gif image of right arrow
  +-up.gif    = .gif image of up arrow
  +-graywall/
  |  |
  |  \+-z1l.gif = frontmost left angled wall image
  |   +-z1m.gif = frontmost flat wall image
  |   +-z1r.gif = frontmost right angled wall image
  |   +-z2l.gif = middle left angled wall image
  |   +-z2m.gif = middle flat wall image
  |   +-z2r.gif = middle right angled wall image
  |   +-z3l.gif = farthest left angled wall image
  |   +-z3m.gif = farthest flat wall image
  |   +-z3r.gif = farthest right angled wall image
  |   +-z1s.gif = frontmost side flat wall image
  |   +-z2s.gif = middle side flat wall image
  |   +-z3s.gif = farthest side  wall image
  +-floor
  |  |
  |  \+-backn.gif = background image for north facing "rooms"
  |   +-backs.gif = background image for south facing "rooms"
  |   +-backw.gif = background image for west facing "rooms"
  |   +-backe.gif = background image for east facing "rooms"
  |   +-backt.gif = tile image for map.html
  +-compn.gif  = picture of a compass pointing north
  +-comps.gif  = picture of a compass pointing south
  +-compw.gif  = picture of a compass pointing west
  +-compe.gif  = picture of a compass pointing east
  +-mlink.gif  = picture of imaglink to map.html from room file
  +-z4m.gif    = blank image for "out of sight" part of a room
  +-spacer.gif = spacer image for room files

  @{"Back" link MAIN}

@ENDNODE

